<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 24 at 7:52PM EDT  by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>...LOCALLY DENSE FOG TONIGHT...
Areas of fog tonight will frequently reduce visibility to less
than one mile. Visibility could be as low as one quarter mile at
times where fog is locally dense. Travelers this evening into
overnight should prepare for rapid reductions in visibility. Slow
down, and allow extra time to reach your destination safely.
Visibility will improve as the fog dissipates by pre-dawn hours.
The fog will persist longest across Cape Cod and the Islands,
where poor visibility could linger into the early morning hours.</description>
